This landscape is just magical with its monochromatic hues and wind-carved rocks. While I've been excited to explore places like these for a long time, I've also been apprehensive about capturing the essence of its awesomeness in a photograph. While a single exposure may do justice to some extent, it takes skill to blend shots and bring out the intricate details of the dynamic interplay of light and shadows in this environment. Though I have some shots that show potential, I'm struggling to achieve the desired effect. Might be time to check out a photography workshop somewhere 👀✨ #gameoftones #monochromatic #canyonx #wanderlust #lightroomedits #camerasettings #beforeandafter
Instagram vs. Reality - Italian Edition 🇮🇹

A photo that will never be as crazy as the photo of us taking this photo 🥸

Short story time! Woke up in Utah, drove to Arizona… and needed to catch a flight in Vegas. But YOLO, we *needed to check out the Valley of Fire for sunset before heading out. Pressed on the gas, got a speeding ticket (not gonna get into that 👀😂) but hours later here we were… 30 minutes till sunset and worth it. Plot Twist !!! Park rangers literally drive through the park grabbing everyone who is still *parked to escort them out of the area. NO ONE IS ALLOWED AFTER SUNSET! I like to think I am a quick photographer… but uffff this time I really thought “This amazing landscape is just for the eyes. No way I can catch a proper composition this quick” … as we, and many others, were escorted out I told Ashley “Alright, you drive now, I’ll drop the 70-200 and I’ll hang out the window of the car like a dog trying to bite the air. Please please please don’t let a rock fly into the lens.” Within 10 minutes out, this shot popped up! Sky turned cotton candy color, cars disappeared under the hill in front of us, road became the most gorgeous leading line into the canyon… it was NOW or NEVER. Told Ashley to drive on the wrong side of the road for a split second to better center the yellow line on the road and boom! MISSION ACCOMPLISHED !!! 

Now, was it all worth it?! You tell me ✨

#valleyoffire #lightroomedits #camerasetup #gameoftones #goldenhour #leadinglines #wanderlust

Up at 4 am, tackling Crater Lake for a sunrise shot. Thought the roads were blocked, ended up snow-hiking like for hours … aaand turned out, there's a parking lot right at "the spot"! 😂 No “regerts” though! Views were epic and the fact we were there entirely by ourselves was insane.

Got a shot of Wizard Island, but it's a puzzle. 7 exposures deep and plan to blend them with Raya Pro. Pressure's on to make it spotless, but perfection's a process. ✨

Oregon, you're something else – one of the coolest states on the map. 🌲 

#craterlake #oregonexplored #pacificnorthwest #sunriseoftheday #agameoftones #lightroomedits #beforeandafter

All roads lead to the Milky Way. ✨

Chased that Zion sunset, got rained out – classic! 😅 Instead of sulking, flipped the script and took on the Milky Way at dawn. 🌌 PhotoPills said it was gonna be tricky, but hey, challenge accepted! 😎 Woke up at 4 am, geared up, and embarked on the quest. Almost gave up, but a little extra drive led to the jackpot: mountain, Milky Way, and a road with the coolest leading lines. 

Not an Astro pro, but damn, this shot is now one of my favorites. 🚀 

#zionnationalpark #milkyway #leadinglines #utahgram #milkywaychasers #nevergiveup #camerasettings #sony

Talk about a frame within the frame 🇨🇴 

Dope vibes from Guatapé, Colombia. Was tempted to share the vibrant streets, but couldn't pass up on this composition. The church and the perfectly arranged tree leaves in the foreground create their own compelling scene. Favorite shot of the day for sure 📷 

Side note, I’m still thinking about the bandeja paisa I ate here for lunch 🤤

This epic waterfall view near Portland is easily accessible, but beware – it can turn into a crowd nightmare! 👀

Massive shout out to our patient friends @yingwanster and @lixualan, for taking us there knowing well the challenges ahead. 🙌

While the idea of a dramatic shot with me as a tiny subject at the bridge crossed my mind… I decided nah, not worth it 😅
